    {
      "id": "a1b2c3d4-0011-4000-a000-000000000017",
      "name": "About this workflow",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [180, 60],
      "parameters": {
        "width": 1400,
        "height": 260,
        "content": "## WF-MS-2 -- GHL -> Hostfully Outbound (Poll Mode)\n\n**Trigger:** Schedule every 2 minutes (polls GHL for recent outbound messages)\n**Why poll?** GHL does not expose a free OutboundMessage webhook via API or PIT tokens.\nThe paid GHL Automation trigger (Option A) or a Marketplace App (Option C) would enable real-time push.\n\n**Flow:** Poll window (last 3 min) -> GET /conversations/search (50 most recent) -> per conversation: GET messages -> filter outbound + recent -> MessageDedup check -> Search Opportunities for contact -> extract hostfully_thread_uid from active Opportunity -> POST to Hostfully thread -> on success: append dedup + mark GHL delivered; on failure: log to MessagingErrors.\n\n**Multi-booking safe:** Uses Opportunities (not contact custom fields) so each booking has its own thread UID.\n\n**Config IDs:**\n- Pipeline: 5mNaQ5aMF70J8l6bVFyq | Thread UID field: dzc0UzKrnbqQ4bkpVfPi\n- GHL credential is already set (VwJj55d4veBRjPmF)."
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "a1b2c3d4-0012-4000-a000-000000000018",
      "name": "Scale and Limits",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [180, 360],
      "parameters": {
        "width": 500,
        "height": 380,
        "color": 3,
        "content": "## Scale -- Are We Safe?\n\nYes, at David's current size. Here is why:\n\n**50 conversations per poll**\nWe grab the 50 most recently active conversations each run. David has maybe 10-30 active bookings at any time, so we always catch everything. This would only become a problem if 50+ guests all messaged within the same 2-minute window -- basically impossible in a small STR operation.\n\n**10 messages per conversation**\nWe read the last 10 messages from each thread. In practice, an agent reply is 1-2 messages at a time. You would need to send 10+ messages to the same guest in under 2 minutes for one to slip through -- not a real scenario.\n\n**2-minute delay**\nReplies from GHL reach the guest within ~2 minutes (not instant). Fine for normal back-and-forth. If this ever feels too slow, upgrading to Option A (paid GHL trigger) drops it to near-instant.\n\n**When would limits actually matter?**\nIf the operation scaled to 100+ properties with constant guest messaging, or if automated GHL workflows fire dozens of messages per minute. At that point, switch to Option A or build a Marketplace App."
      }
    }
